<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="F56" captionText="Figure 56. Distribution of Solanum villosum Mill." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure56" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305355" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">56</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum villosum" order="Solanales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Solanum villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to Europe where it is very common around the Mediterranean basin, the Arabian Peninsula to dry sub-tropical Asia, and eastern Africa (where it is cultivated for its fruit); the species is locally introduced but not persistent and not yet naturalised in North America.
</paragraph>
